name: Semimpi Hotel Bali
address: Jl. Kuwum 1 No.24, Kerobokan Kelod, Kec. Kuta Utara, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
Amazing place yet affordable!
They foster a lot of dogs and cats around the hotel.

If you‚Äôre staying here, please give LUKY and CHLEO some hugs and foods! (Dogs)
They‚Äôre the best üíï
review 2: A lovely place, worth the money, the staffs are great, they even feed the cats and dogs who roamed freelly around the area. The only problem is only the lady who rent the room annually, a bit nosy and bossy. However, Will be back here for sure
review 3: Looks exactly in the photos! Very decent and affordable stay! Room is clean and you can watch cable channels on the TV! My room is on the first floor so the back door links to the common area where you can sit, chill or eat. Staff are friendly and helpful! The location is slightly away from the main Canggu area. It gets really dark at night so would be safe for ladies to take a gojek/grab car in and out. Overall, pleasant stay! Will recommend those who are looking for an affordable and decent place!
review 4:
Despite my 5-hour late check-in due to a health issue upon arriving in Bali, the staff patiently waited for me.

The affordable price of the room pleasantly surprised me, as it turned out to be spacious with a comfortable bathroom. The location is also convenient, allowing easy exploration of Canggu or Seminyak. Additionally, there are nearby amenities such as an Indomaret convenience store (within walking distance) and Pepito.
review 5: Semimpi Hotel in Bali is a fantastic place to stay if you're looking for a calm and peaceful environment. The hotel is incredibly clean and well-maintained, making it a comfortable and enjoyable place to work remotely. I stayed there for a month and it was definitely the right choice. The only issue I encountered was occasional internet connectivity problems, but the staff was quick to address and resolve any issues. Overall, I highly recommend this hotel for anyone looking for a calm and relaxing stay in Bali.

name: Delicioso Bistro & Restaurant

The Cordon Bleu was great, not dry! Fish & Chips was nice and well flavored. I tried their Nasi Goreng Kecombrang, it was so tasty and very fragrant. We nibbled on their cheese pretzels as well before the food arrived and they‚Äôre actually very yumm. Approved by my French friend!
review 2:

name: DEVA BALI APARTMENT
address: Jl. Baliku II No.Kav. 88, Kerobokan, Kec. Kuta Utara, Denpasar, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
So disappointed from the first minute I arrived. In reception they said that they don‚Äôt have rooms , but they didn‚Äôt inform me before,bcs I did reservation so they probably could send me some email but no they make me wait In reception and promise provide car to their another hotel. But after 30min of waiting I just ordered grab and paid by my own even they said they will give me money back but first its such a waist of time! Another place has good location but rooms are dirty , even they said this place is better then I book.
It‚Äôs worth money u pay for it but service and cleaning so bad !
review 2: Not as good as in the pic. There are stains on the roof in my room. The elevator is super slow, so i prefer to use the stairs. And when i wanted to sleep, the blanket totally smelly. I think from the last customer. Because it smells like an odor mix men's perfume. The room is clean, and the staff are nice. The area is also good, quite close to a restaurant or mini market. U get breakfast, there's soap, shampoo & towels. But bring ur own toothpaste & brush. There's a small kitchen on the corner that u can use.
review 3:
I recently had the pleasure of staying at this fantastic apartment, and I must say, it exceeded all my expectations. The service provided was truly excellent, and the staff went above and beyond to ensure my stay was comfortable and enjoyable.

From the moment I arrived, the staff welcomed me with warm smiles and made the check-in process seamless. They were always readily available to assist with any questions or requests I had throughout my stay, and their helpfulness and genuine care truly made a difference.

The apartment itself was well-maintained and beautifully designed. It was spacious, clean, and had all the amenities I needed for a pleasant stay. The comfortable bed ensured a good night's sleep, and the kitchenette was equipped with everything necessary to prepare meals.

One of the standout features of this apartment is its strategic location. Situated in a prime area, it offered easy access to various attractions, shopping centers, and public transportation. I was able to explore the city effortlessly, and the convenience of having everything within reach was a major plus.

I was thoroughly impressed with the overall experience at this apartment. The combination of exceptional service, helpful staff, and strategic location made my stay truly memorable. I highly recommend this place to anyone looking for a comfortable and convenient accommodation option. I will definitely be returning on my next visit to the city!
review 4:
The bathroom just needs a full blown clean with chemicals, if the 50+ holes on the shower nossle only 2 worked resulting in ridiculous water pressure that shoots the hose in all directions. The soap dispenser was broken and put back together like a puzzle piece which would get knocked off the wall by the shower.

The room was clean, except for under the bed which I only realised when checking if I'd forgotten anything

Good value for money but I'm glad we only stayed for 1 night.
review 5: Considering the relatively cheap price, it's not a bad experience. They got a bonus of petite kitchen area with some utensils, pretty strategic location, and tasty breakfast delivered to our room. What's unfortunate is that the room was not in a good condition with some wall paint were peeling off, the lighting were a bit dim, the bathroom mirror were broken. Oh, and they barely have parking lot (only for 2-3 cars)

name: 1959 Cocktail Bar & Dance Club

The cocktails ARE AMAZING! highly recommend trusting the suggestion of the staff as everything they suggested was literally mind blowing .
The dj was also great I loved the vibe and stayed until very late .
I will definitely go back again
review 2:
A modern prestigious cocktail bar! Have a cocktails experience with the 1959 legendary stories.
Atmosphere was lit very chill and cozy. They also have a good service and knowledgeable staff.
Juat enjoy the different ambience!
review 3: Magnificent. Came here 2 days in a row. Must try Shirakaba, will suprise your taste of buds. Its not only ordinary drink, its fusion between food and drink. Atmosphere very chill, cozy, but also funky for dance love. Just enjoy the different ambience.
review 4:
Went into this hidden bar by accident, was surprised by the quality of drinks and service here

Order Shirakaba and u won‚Äôt go wrong
review 5:
Definitely my best cocktails bar experience so far. Cocktails really good, And there have very nice good vibes and and they have very good entertainment,
I really love the live music there. The staff very helpfull . I remember one staff the named , Marsha this lady really know how to treat us very well thank you .. was so much fun and definetely will come back!

name: Villa Tukad Alit/KISARA
address: Jl. Raya Kerobokan No.12, Kerobokan Kelod, Kec. Kuta Utara, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: Really love our stay here for 6 days!!! The swimming pool was the reason we stayed here and glad we really loved it. As its in a tropical area/country do expect lizards here and there but overall we really love it. Their staffs here are also accommodating to us, manage to rent a bike here and have our laundry done with a cost too! Recommended to all. Thanks to all for making our stay here amazing and also dont be surprised but theres a kitty cat here too!
review 2:
PLEASE SAVE YOUR MONEY...

THIS PLACE IS INFESTED WITH BUGS AND THEY KNOW IT! After expressing frustration, I was giving a can of bug spray to deal with it myself. They tried to accommodate me by having me change rooms but they problem was worst in the second villa. A day into my stay I had to change my hotel for this reason and they refused to refund my money. They took no accountability for the issue and it is my hope that no on else experience this horrid place.
review 3: The villa is huge, indoor pool is the best, great places to stay with friends and family. The service they provide is amazing. Eazy access to bars and restaurants, their food also great. Definitely worth it.
review 4:
Really fantastic stay here for 12 days!
Place was neat and clean (cleaned each day too) tucked away from the main areas (which is what we wanted) but still only a 10 Min drive so still very convinient.
The service was great, staff really did their best to accommodate and even made partners birthday special!!
All were really Friendly, definately trustworthy and was easy to communicate with.
Breakfast delivered each day which was also great quality.
The villas are open living area with pool to the outside, but closed bedrooms for evenings, and with the location being a bit out gave a great Bali experience.
The price point was spot on for what you got so was very good value and despite the Google 3 star rating, the team does their best to give you a 5 star experience.
Would return again in an instant!
review 5: the bed sounds, the pool has high chlorine. but overall its a good villa

name: Lighthouse - Cafe, Bar & Lounge - Event Spaces - Podcast & Video Studios
address: Jl. Raya Kerobokan No.5X, Kerobokan Kelod, Kec. Kuta Utara, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
At Light House Studio in Kerobokan, Bali, coffee aficionados will delight in their exceptional coffee beverages, accompanied by a menu of delicious food options, albeit without croissants.

The expansive space provides ample room to work comfortably, with lightning-fast wifi catering perfectly to digital workers and nomads alike.

Additionally, they offer studio rental for YouTubers, adding versatility to their offerings. However, the downside lies in the restroom facilities, with only two rooms available and limited space, which may prove inconvenient during peak hours.

Nevertheless, with its convenient location, ample parking, excellent wifi, and conducive ambiance, Light House Studio stands out as an ideal workspace for digital marketers.
review 2:
COFFEE : GOOD! PLACE : GOOD! SERVICE : Ok. TOILET : Clean. PRICE : Fair.

Thanks again to ‚ÄúGoogle Map‚Äù for making me here.

When you come here, get slow while driving until you find ‚ÄúExpat‚Äù, means you are at the right place.

This place was combined with studio also.

Myself, Im looking for the ‚ÄúGreen-View‚Äù, so when I entered the door I asked the staff to direct me to the back.

This place was Good for me, its atmosphere, the guests and the ambience. It was no crowded and most guests are working here.

As usual before I start my work, I had my Cappucino then enjoy working here.

The staffs are well. The Toilet was clean, no smell and dry (nice).

I reccommend this place for working, couple, friend, small group and couple.
review 3: Honestly, best studio for podcasting and hosting events! Firstly, they have 3 studios, each serves different purpose. We used Studio 1 (biggest) for our Women In Business Networking Event. Secondly, support we received from the Lighthouse management team was heartwarming!
review 4: Great place for working. I really love the vibe here. The only downside is the parking, which is sometimes hardly accessible due to traffic jam on the road in front of jt. üòÉ

name: Ayam Kampung & Rawon Bu Ros
address: Jl. Raya Semer No.59B, Kerobokan, Kec. Kuta Utara, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: light broth, aromatic and with a squeeze of lime very balanced and clean flavors with tender shank and marrow. The fried Tempe is also very good. The rice is sub-par but that‚Äôs du rigueur in Bali would have loved a bowl of quality Jasmine rice. Very VERY bright and clean with friendly service. An excellent value.
review 2:
Best fried chicken and rawon in Bali!
They only use free range chicken, and comes with lots of kremes. Their rawon is also good and authentic just like in east java.

Also recommended to try their crispy chicken skin and also deep fried cabbage.
review 3:
This place was near our accommodation but we only tried it because our driver recommended, and it was THE BEST local food!!

Really nice and friendly people who were helpful in explaining what each food was.

Our favourite and only thing we ate was the ayam goreng thigh, the first one on the menu. Everything cooked to perfection, the taste, the rice, the chilli, all put together is out of this world.

After discovering this place we had to eat this at least once a day and tried the tempeh and fried cabbages which I really like too. Fried cabbage might feel a bit oily but good crunch.

Will definitely come back here when in Bali!

review 5: Honestly love this type of fried chicken, so savory! Rawon was legit! First time trying it and will re-order the food. Also available for online food delivery via Grab or Gojek.

name: Happy Mie
address: Jl. Raya Semer No.40 B, Kerobokan, Kec. Kuta Utara, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
I am a Chinese and I must say the kway Teow was thick and chewy, though still not the same as the ones we usually eat in Singapore and Malaysia, but was the only thing in this order that tasted ok.

The rest of the toppings (aside the vegetables) were not even close to our the usual meat and dumpling taste, in fact, they just felt wrong, I think (couldn't remember) dumpling filling were not even minced meat, those small chunks of meat taste powdery and strange. The bakso (chewy floury meat ball) was really...ü§¢ Maybe other food in the menu may taste better.
review 2: My favorite pork noodle ever. The broth is originally pork. The noodle is so soft just as i like. I am from sulawesi and the tiny cut of happy mie noodle is my preference. They make their sambal using their old recipe and it is the best. I like pork nasi goreng, campur 2 paket dan mie babi happy mie. The meatball in bakwan campur is just okay and the texture is hard tho. Not as soft as indinesian meatball in common.
review 3: Pork belly noodle is highly recommended, however other dishes are not too bad at all
review 4: A restaurant that not only specialized in noodles but also has wide variety of other Chinese food menu such as vermicelli noodles, char kuew tiaw, fried rice and many more. The price are reasonable and the taste was also pretty good. Definitely recommended for noodles lover or want something stir fried.
review 5: Been so long i havent try Chinese dishes üòÇ craving for it for sure. Overall taste so good

With reasonable prices, refreshing fruit juices, and excellent service, Bems Resto has become my go-to spot, especially when craving a veggie-packed option in the area. name: Warung Sate Madura Pak Awi
address: Jl. Raya Semer No.15, Kerobokan Kelod, Kec. Kuta Utara, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: The chicken satays were juicy, tender, and well-grilled. I love the fact that they were meaty with no skins. But biggest surprise came from the lamb curry, it was very good! Tasty, meaty, flavorful soup - perfect pairing with the rice. Loved them overall.
review 2: Delicious sate and tongseng kambing!! If you wanna try the authentic taste of Madura Satay, this is the right place in Canggu Area!!
review 3:
Always be my favorite since few years ago (more than 4 years already).
Pak Awi and his staffs are kind and we can also get tasty Gulai Kambing here.
review 4: For a quick delicious sate kambing and gule.. this ia the place
review 5:
Expect the best satay when you are here!
Both the mutton (kambing & chicken satay were amazing as well as  gulai. Both satay came with amazing peanut sauce.
Truth to be told, I was not a fan of mutton dishes. I tend to find mutton dish too gamey in both taste and smell. This was obviously not the case in Pak Awi's stall. The satay contains a bit of organ meat and fat which  normally would taste absolutely gamey for me, even these part are not gamey at all. Delicious and relish. Pricewise, it cost us IDR 90K for 2 portion of gulai, 1 portion chicken satay, 1 portion mutton satay, 1 portion rice, 1 portion lontong (rice cake), 1 ice tea and 1 temulawak (it is like soda pop with herbs taste), given the portion we got and considering that mutton is expensive meat, it is very fairly priced and definitely money worth. Highly recommended. Please come here and taste the authentic Madura satay.
Well done pak Awi.

review 1:
I stayed here a few years ago when the building just finished the renovation. Fyi, the road is only for bikes (cars can not come inside the alley). So moving in was hard. The wall was not great due to the leaking marks from the bathroom. It was humid.
The good thing is they have a separate area for the kitchen. Cooking was easy!
Anyway, we moved out from this place because the owner did not want to repair the wall & they were hard to talk to. It is based on my experience so other people might have a different experience.
review 2: Good room,good vibe
